title: Boys cross country rankings for Oct. 12, 2015
text:
Parkland's Hailemichael Geiger (left) and Daniel Kyvelos (center) lead the No. 2-ranked Trojans. (Sue Beyer | For lehighvalleylive.com) By Brad Wilson | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 12, 2015 1:20 PM, updated October 12, 2015 5:32 PM View/Post Comments 
A few changes in the rankings to reflect improvement by Emmaus and Central Catholic . 
The first of the big postseason meets comes Thursday when Phillipsburg hosts the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex championship at the Phillipsburg Athletic Complex. Should be a fascinating meet. Easton defeated Phillipsburg 19-44 on that course Saturday and looking at times between Voorhees , North Hunterdon and Easton will be fascinating.
